contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:48.215 --> 00:50.425
<i>Mmm! I whispered, "I am too young"</i>

00:50.509 --> 00:52.679
And then "I am old enough"

00:52.762 --> 00:54.471
Wherefore I threw a brown penny

00:54.556 --> 00:56.473
- to find out if I might love
- Who is that?

00:58.017 --> 01:00.645
- That is Yates.
- Who the fuck is Yates?

01:00.728 --> 01:03.648
Oh, just a minor Irish poet...

01:03.731 --> 01:05.817
Whoever the fuck that is.

01:05.900 --> 01:08.402
Your ignorance is so infectious!

01:12.991 --> 01:16.578
<i>Oh, wait a minute...</i>

01:16.661 --> 01:18.955
Oh, my dear lord...

01:19.038 --> 01:21.749
Oh, Hannah, my love...

01:21.833 --> 01:23.166
Well done!

01:23.250 --> 01:25.795
Keep going.
I want to hear the rest of the poem.

01:25.878 --> 01:27.589
<i>Love is the wicked thing...</i>

01:38.808 --> 01:41.393
There is no one wise enough to find it out

01:41.476 --> 01:45.898
For he would be thinking of love
till the stars had run from the sky

01:45.982 --> 01:46.982
Disgusting.

01:47.900 --> 01:51.111
- On his bowl.
- Hey, do you want some of this?

01:51.194 --> 01:53.280
Well, I'll try anything twice.

02:43.665 --> 02:46.000
- There you go. Keep the change.
- OK, thank you.

02:48.086 --> 02:50.420
- Fenton Dillane, my man!
- Irving, how are you?

02:50.504 --> 02:51.923
Good.

02:56.218 --> 02:58.763
How's the family? Baby Lou?

03:00.932 --> 03:02.850
Baby Lou ain't a baby no more.

03:02.934 --> 03:04.686
She's a three-year-old wrecking ball.

03:06.228 --> 03:08.690
That Cali sun got you soft.

03:08.773 --> 03:10.900
It's not that sunny in San Francisco.

03:10.983 --> 03:12.192
No?

03:12.902 --> 03:14.444
Don't tell me you're a Nets fan now...

03:14.528 --> 03:16.613
Come on, man, Knicks for life!

03:16.698 --> 03:18.700
I gotta give Phil some time to build.

03:21.703 --> 03:23.055
Man, it's really great seeing you.

03:23.079 --> 03:24.413
Hey, man, good seeing you too.

03:24.496 --> 03:26.040
Don't be away so long, OK?

03:26.791 --> 03:28.071
- I got it from here.
- You sure?

03:28.126 --> 03:29.376
Yeah.

03:34.924 --> 03:37.342
- Very pungent.
- That means it's dead.

03:42.932 --> 03:45.392
- Mom?
- All right.

03:45.475 --> 03:46.728
Oh, it's Fenton.

03:47.394 --> 03:50.397
Fenton, this is a surprise.

03:51.273 --> 03:53.025
Wasn't expecting...
You're home!

03:55.737 --> 03:57.362
Yeah. New me.

03:57.446 --> 03:58.572
What's up, buddy?

03:58.655 --> 03:59.531
John.

03:59.614 --> 04:02.952
Thank you... John.

04:03.577 --> 04:06.914
Didn't think I wanted to be home for...
the latest?

04:06.998 --> 04:09.666
I wasn't sure.

04:13.004 --> 04:14.546
Oh, shoot, the sea bass.

04:15.006 --> 04:18.091
If someone's near the oven
would you shut it off?

04:18.176 --> 04:19.844
It's good, man?

04:19.927 --> 04:22.429
Things good in San Fran?

04:22.512 --> 04:25.099
Haven't seen you in, what, a year?

04:25.183 --> 04:26.433
- Yeah. I guess.
- Yeah.

04:26.934 --> 04:28.936
Were you just selling my mom weed?

04:29.020 --> 04:30.855
Oh, strictly at cost.

04:30.938 --> 04:32.272
She... she smokes weed?

04:32.355 --> 04:33.900
Oh, yeah...

04:33.983 --> 04:36.359
No... not a lot.

04:36.443 --> 04:37.945
Sometimes.

04:39.197 --> 04:42.033
Listen, The Georgian's having people
over tomorrow night.

04:42.116 --> 04:45.203
- Good old Georgian party.
- Yeah.

04:45.285 --> 04:48.497
Fenton, come say hi to your sister,
and there's someone I want you to meet.

04:48.580 --> 04:50.332
Be right there.

04:55.171 --> 04:56.923
Well, well, well...

04:57.006 --> 04:58.507
Layla.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.759
Welcome home, brother.

05:02.677 --> 05:04.972
Fenton, this is my friend, Ahmed.

05:06.598 --> 05:09.351
- Nice to meet you.
- OK. Hello.

05:10.144 --> 05:13.480
Layla, would you be a dear and,
open another bottle of wine?

05:13.563 --> 05:15.482
Oh, yeah. I'm on it.

05:20.238 --> 05:21.864
Layla, let me,
give you a hand with that.

05:21.948 --> 05:23.615
I can...

05:27.619 --> 05:28.830
What is going on?

05:28.913 --> 05:31.040
- What?
- I mean who is he?

05:31.123 --> 05:32.707
He's a friend of Mom's.

05:32.791 --> 05:36.879
They met at a Studies of The Far East
group at the Met.

05:36.963 --> 05:41.300
So, what, they go to museums, they look at
ceramics from the Khyber Pass, like...?

05:43.593 --> 05:45.930
If his presence is so offensive to you,

05:46.013 --> 05:48.640
just give notice the next time
you feel like visiting.

05:50.101 --> 05:51.434
Wow.

05:51.518 --> 05:53.145
- Are they like...
- Fucking?

05:53.229 --> 05:54.981
Jesus, Layla!

05:55.064 --> 05:56.899
I hope so.

05:56.983 --> 05:59.193
But Mom's not Dad,
so I wouldn't count on it.

06:03.906 --> 06:05.908
It's big of you to come home for this.

06:07.243 --> 06:08.702
Back for what?

06:11.454 --> 06:12.706
You tell me.

06:13.582 --> 06:14.959
What, back for Dad?

06:17.377 --> 06:20.089
I wrote something I'm not sure
I want to publish.

06:20.923 --> 06:22.716
What's going on, Fenton?

06:28.097 --> 06:30.057
It doesn't work like that.

06:30.141 --> 06:32.642
You don't get to leave the way you did

06:32.726 --> 06:35.478
and then come back
and expect everything to be OK.

06:35.562 --> 06:39.566
Because you just left, for a long time.

06:40.483 --> 06:42.880
You would too if every New York asshole
with a blog or a column

06:42.904 --> 06:46.489
was comparing you to bags of douche
or Alec fucking Baldwin.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.911
They're just reacting to the what, Fenton,
not the who.

06:52.330 --> 06:54.664
If you ever leave like that again...

06:55.832 --> 06:57.584
I'm gonna kill you.

06:58.961 --> 07:01.546
Seriously. I'm gonna kill you.

07:02.924 --> 07:05.508
OK. Never again.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.345
I promise.

07:15.937 --> 07:20.024
Layla, what are you...
studying in college?

07:21.400 --> 07:22.484
Lots of stuff.

07:23.443 --> 07:26.613
Really, just a four year delay
to my unemployment.

07:27.239 --> 07:31.410
Lay, are you still,
dating that guy with the... red hair?

07:31.493 --> 07:32.744
What was his name, Dick?

07:32.827 --> 07:35.414
He had braces, yeah? And a mullet.

07:35.497 --> 07:37.457
- A mullet?
- Fuck both of you.

07:37.540 --> 07:39.709
And who are you dating right now?

07:39.793 --> 07:41.503
I came back for Jessie.

07:43.588 --> 07:44.631
Fenton...

07:46.050 --> 07:50.929
why don't we smoke some of this
lovely, purple marijuana

07:51.013 --> 07:52.264
that you brought, John?

07:52.348 --> 07:54.141
- Mom...
- What?

07:54.225 --> 07:56.685
You walked in on the deal.

07:58.145 --> 08:01.983
Regardless, you can take pride in the fact
that this is some excellent shit.

08:02.066 --> 08:03.275
Yeah.

08:03.359 --> 08:05.194
I'll get it.

08:08.947 --> 08:11.117
Hello?

08:11.866 --> 08:13.910
Really?

08:13.995 --> 08:16.122
We're eating dinner, you cocksucker!

08:18.498 --> 08:20.292
Which cocksucker was that?

08:20.376 --> 08:23.097
It was another one of those reporters
asking if I had anything to say

08:23.129 --> 08:24.546
about my father.

09:48.130 --> 09:49.839
Happy you're back.

09:54.345 --> 09:57.389
Ma... are you...
You OK?

09:58.474 --> 10:00.642
Me? I'm fine.

10:02.561 --> 10:06.606
Oh, you mean the... marijuana.

10:06.689 --> 10:09.443
It helps me... relax.

10:13.280 --> 10:15.491
I wasn't talking about that.

10:16.408 --> 10:17.617
Oh.

10:19.411 --> 10:23.081
No, I was just... you know, about Dad.

10:24.082 --> 10:26.293
Him! It'll be fine.

10:29.380 --> 10:30.922
I was going to go see him tomorrow.

10:31.798 --> 10:33.425
That's what you're back for.

10:36.845 --> 10:38.514
Yeah, sure. You know, for Pop.

10:39.889 --> 10:41.433
I'm working on something...

10:42.100 --> 10:44.145
and could use his advice.

10:45.854 --> 10:47.814
It's good to have you home.

10:49.150 --> 10:51.485
You look... thin.

11:20.222 --> 11:22.682
So far, Fenton, these chapters...

11:23.517 --> 11:25.561
Wow! I mean...

11:25.644 --> 11:27.605
I mean, they're hilarious.

11:29.231 --> 11:31.609
I loved your story,<i> The Birthday Party.</i>

11:31.691 --> 11:34.361
Really? You know it forced me into exile.

11:35.487 --> 11:36.821
I'm serious.

11:36.905 --> 11:39.366
And this novel picks up
right where that left off.

11:39.450 --> 11:42.952
I feel like we know these people.
That they exist.

11:43.036 --> 11:46.332
And after the reception of the story,
it's totally marketable.

11:46.415 --> 11:48.542
Because we do it like one of those memoirs

11:48.626 --> 11:51.836
where we're not sure if what we're reading
really happened or not.

11:52.837 --> 11:55.131
But James, this is... this is fiction.

11:55.216 --> 11:56.716
Well, of course it is.

11:56.799 --> 12:00.429
Now, when do you think you'll be finished?

12:32.085 --> 12:34.421
You're home! Huh.

12:34.505 --> 12:36.590
Look at this.

12:36.674 --> 12:38.717
Front page.

12:39.593 --> 12:44.055
Of course, the turds weren't interested
when I won my National Book Award, but...

12:44.138 --> 12:46.267
Was that girl that was just here,

12:46.350 --> 12:48.142
was she from the car crash?

12:48.226 --> 12:50.061
Yeah.

12:51.313 --> 12:52.648
She's an excellent writer.

12:54.608 --> 12:57.695
Well, this should be a lesson
for you and your sister:

12:58.654 --> 13:01.155
Always wear seat belts.

13:01.239 --> 13:02.782
If I hadn't been wearing a seatbelt,

13:02.865 --> 13:06.035
you'd be standing
over a headstone right now.

13:06.119 --> 13:08.204
Why didn't you just leave Mom years ago?

13:08.289 --> 13:10.416
I can't leave your mother.

13:10.499 --> 13:12.875
She understands me.

13:14.336 --> 13:17.213
This is humiliating.

13:17.298 --> 13:19.717
Oh, I know. For all of us.

13:19.799 --> 13:22.176
Oh, you don't know the half of it.

13:23.136 --> 13:25.138
Well, then again, maybe you do.

13:25.221 --> 13:27.223
This does contradict your public image.

13:27.308 --> 13:29.267
Well, not only that,

13:29.351 --> 13:33.522
the other girl's parents are suing me
and the university.

13:36.274 --> 13:39.403
All of these young girls
throwing themselves at me,

13:39.486 --> 13:41.530
you'd think your mother would understand...

13:41.613 --> 13:43.490
Keep it in your pants, Dad.
Don't blame Mom!

13:43.574 --> 13:45.409
No, no. I'm not blaming her.

13:45.492 --> 13:47.869
I'm just saying it's not all my fault.

13:47.952 --> 13:49.538
What the f...

13:49.621 --> 13:51.164
Are you writing?

13:52.081 --> 13:53.934
Yeah, I wanted to talk to you
about this publisher...

13:53.958 --> 13:57.713
By the way, those bastards were
just waiting to tear apart your story.

13:57.796 --> 13:58.838
They had it out for you.

13:58.921 --> 14:01.633
They wanted to tear your story apart
right from the beginning.

14:01.717 --> 14:04.969
It's just the way it is. Sons of bitches.

14:05.053 --> 14:08.599
Anyway, I'm glad you made it
down here for this.

14:08.682 --> 14:13.061
You've been off the radar
for quite a long time.

14:15.897 --> 14:17.065
I look good here.

14:17.148 --> 14:20.402
That's a damn good picture of me.

14:36.918 --> 14:38.670
I saw Dad today.

14:41.465 --> 14:44.551
Yeah, if we had any sense
we'd just leave him there to rot.

14:47.763 --> 14:49.473
Have you seen Dad cry?

14:50.306 --> 14:53.309
No. That's so random. Why?

14:55.103 --> 14:58.022
I don't know, just... just thinking.

14:58.106 --> 14:59.483
Well, you shouldn't.

15:00.776 --> 15:02.861
- We already know he's a fucking prick.
- Enough!

15:03.779 --> 15:05.321
Whatever.

15:08.700 --> 15:10.702
I'm going to The Georgian's tonight.

15:10.786 --> 15:12.871
You are?

15:12.954 --> 15:15.248
Yeah. He's having a party.

15:15.331 --> 15:16.916
Why don't you come?

15:18.251 --> 15:20.169
I thought you hated him?

15:21.588 --> 15:23.297
I do.

15:24.675 --> 15:25.967
What?

15:26.926 --> 15:28.261
Nothing.

16:21.482 --> 16:25.443
- That is how we fucking do it in Tbilisi.
- Where's that?

16:25.527 --> 16:27.195
Georgia.

16:27.278 --> 16:28.864
The Republic of Georgia.

16:28.947 --> 16:30.491
Oh, my cousin went to Georgia Tech.

16:30.574 --> 16:32.910
No, listen, where Joseph Stalin is from.

16:32.992 --> 16:34.912
Where the original Santa Claus is from.

16:34.994 --> 16:37.581
Where the most beautiful food
in the world...

16:38.832 --> 16:39.917
What the fuck?

16:39.999 --> 16:42.586
Yo, holy shit! Fenton!

16:44.253 --> 16:45.881
When'd you get back in fucking town?

16:45.964 --> 16:48.341
- Yesterday.
- Oh, my God, it's been a long time!

16:48.424 --> 16:51.219
- Yo, how are you holding up?
- Oh, man, I'm good.

16:51.302 --> 16:53.012
Your fucking dad though, huh?

16:53.095 --> 16:55.306
Man after my own heart though, huh?

16:55.389 --> 16:57.643
Fuck, Fenton!
Let's get a fucking drink.

16:57.726 --> 16:59.520
- Yes, please!
- Come on. Holy shit, Fenton!

16:59.603 --> 17:01.647
You got it.

17:01.730 --> 17:04.147
Can I just squeeze...

17:06.777 --> 17:08.277
Yeah, just...

17:09.487 --> 17:11.405
Nothing? All right.

17:12.073 --> 17:13.366
Hi. Can...

17:13.449 --> 17:15.786
OK. I'm trying to get a drink.

17:15.868 --> 17:18.119
- I see that.
- Maybe I'll just...

17:19.079 --> 17:20.999
No? OK.

17:24.962 --> 17:27.088
Hi. How are you doing?

17:28.840 --> 17:31.300
Johnny, what's up, man!

17:31.384 --> 17:33.094
What's up, dude? Good to see you.

17:33.177 --> 17:35.532
- Can you hook me up with some kind?
- Sorry, boss. I'm off-duty tonight.

17:35.556 --> 17:37.098
All right?

17:37.181 --> 17:38.976
Come on, man. Please.

17:40.476 --> 17:42.395
One-fifty.

17:42.478 --> 17:43.479
Dude...

17:43.564 --> 17:45.439
I'm opening up the chimney for you.

17:45.523 --> 17:47.568
One-fifty? Come on, man, I can't.

17:47.651 --> 17:48.735
Then, I can't help you.

17:48.819 --> 17:51.339
Have your parents put more money
in your checking account, yeah?

17:56.117 --> 17:58.357
- You want to help me out there, or...?
- No, not at all.

17:58.411 --> 17:59.732
- No?
- That was too fun to watch.

17:59.788 --> 18:01.539
Well, now I know what happens when a guy

18:01.623 --> 18:04.417
who can define a credit default swap
starts slinging dope.

18:05.836 --> 18:08.880
It's pretty impressive.
All in the game, yo.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.933
- Hey.
- O.M.M.G!

18:20.017 --> 18:22.268
- Layla.
- The Georgian.

18:22.351 --> 18:23.477
Hi.

18:24.186 --> 18:26.480
- My goodness, you've grown!
- All right, all right.

18:26.564 --> 18:29.275
You're still throwing the best parties
in New York. Congratulations.

18:29.358 --> 18:31.079
Thank you. Look at you,
you're all grown up.

18:31.152 --> 18:32.403
Yeah, it happens.

18:32.486 --> 18:34.781
What are you drinking?
I'll get you something special.

18:34.865 --> 18:35.866
Don't roofie my sister.

18:35.949 --> 18:38.619
Are you kidding me? She's like
my little baby sister, this one.

18:38.702 --> 18:40.787
Gross.

18:40.871 --> 18:43.331
- Hey! John, have a drink.
- All right.

18:43.414 --> 18:45.000
Have a drink... But tell me,

18:45.083 --> 18:47.519
what is your dad gonna do now that
everyone is calling him a fraud?

18:47.543 --> 18:51.464
Same thing I did when this town called me
a fraud. He's gonna leave.

18:51.547 --> 18:53.424
He's not that much of an asshole.

18:54.175 --> 18:57.303
Dad gets dizzy crossing the Washington
Bridge. He's not going anywhere.

18:57.386 --> 18:59.747
- He's a genius, your dad. A genius.
- You would think that.

18:59.806 --> 19:01.808
Pops is like Charlie Sheen with a PHD.

19:10.984 --> 19:12.151
Oh shit...

19:22.328 --> 19:23.454
Shit!

19:23.537 --> 19:24.537
This is bad.

19:27.625 --> 19:29.293
Excuse me. Sorry.

19:29.377 --> 19:31.420
Jess, hey.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.757
I've got nothing to say to you.

19:33.840 --> 19:35.801
Oh, I'll do the talking then. Listen...

19:35.884 --> 19:37.928
Great, I'll be doing the leaving.

19:38.011 --> 19:39.387
Jessie.

19:39.971 --> 19:42.140
Jessie, wait. Jess...

19:42.891 --> 19:44.392
Sorry. Excuse me. Pardon me.

19:44.475 --> 19:46.937
- Whoa!
- I'm sorry.

19:47.020 --> 19:47.938
Hey. Hey!

19:48.021 --> 19:49.480
God, would you stop following me?!

19:49.563 --> 19:51.232
- Give me a break!
- Give you a break?

19:51.315 --> 19:53.026
For what? Leaving?

19:53.110 --> 19:55.277
Or for writing that fucking story?

19:55.528 --> 19:58.197
You know, my parents didn't talk
for months after that.

19:58.990 --> 20:01.993
Hey, you guys, you have to be really
careful what you say around this guy,

20:02.077 --> 20:05.246
because you never know
what's going to end up in print.

20:05.329 --> 20:07.082
- Asshole.
- Jessie...

20:07.833 --> 20:09.583
Jessie...

20:09.667 --> 20:11.252
- Hi.
- Hey.

20:11.335 --> 20:12.713
What do you want?

20:12.796 --> 20:14.672
Don't you think we should talk?

20:14.756 --> 20:16.465
Now?!

20:16.549 --> 20:18.342
We could go somewhere else.

20:18.426 --> 20:21.303
Wow... You are unbelievable.

20:25.474 --> 20:28.103
- That's a big ring.
- You didn't get the invite?

20:29.187 --> 20:30.396
"The invite"?

20:30.479 --> 20:32.481
I invited you to hurt you.

20:34.358 --> 20:37.112
There you go again, love.
Chatting with good-looking strangers.

20:37.611 --> 20:39.572
Victor, this is Fenton.

20:40.907 --> 20:43.492
The... the infamous.

20:46.454 --> 20:48.330
Don't you live in California?

20:49.582 --> 20:50.582
Yeah. I'm back.

20:51.918 --> 20:54.253
- For us?
- No.

20:55.088 --> 20:57.298
No shit.

20:57.381 --> 20:58.925
How thoughtful.

20:59.009 --> 21:00.676
Promise to write nice things about it.

21:03.221 --> 21:05.365
I've never written a bad word
about a church in my life.

21:05.389 --> 21:06.599
How about a gallery?

21:08.726 --> 21:11.687
The wedding is at our gallery.

21:12.730 --> 21:13.982
Yeah.

21:14.065 --> 21:16.026
Yeah, right, right.
That was on the invite.

21:17.359 --> 21:20.822
Sweetie, we need to go. I promised
Matthew and Bjork we'd stop by.

21:20.906 --> 21:22.448
Maybe I'll stop by too.

21:23.657 --> 21:25.618
To the gallery, I mean.

21:25.701 --> 21:27.453
Check out some art.

21:27.536 --> 21:31.457
Well if you're serious about
contemporary art, please, come by anytime.

21:31.540 --> 21:33.168
Yeah, no, I'm serious about it.

21:33.251 --> 21:35.212
About contemporary art. I love it.

21:35.294 --> 21:38.006
- I'll definitely stop by.
- Great.

21:38.799 --> 21:41.176
Well it has to be before Saturday.

21:42.718 --> 21:43.719
OK.

21:43.804 --> 21:46.514
The wedding is this Saturday, Fenton.

21:49.226 --> 21:51.019
This...
Wait, this Saturday?

21:52.645 --> 21:54.064
It was on the invite.

21:57.984 --> 21:58.985
Good to meet you.

22:33.311 --> 22:34.311
Rough night?

22:36.314 --> 22:39.567
- Yeah.
- We have to leave soon.

22:39.650 --> 22:42.778
Your father wants us all there
when he's released from the hospital.

